Name: brachydactyly type A1B
Definition: A brachydactyly type A1 characterized by shortened middle phalanges of all the digits and shortened proximal phalanges of the thumbs and big toes but normal stature that has_material_basis_in variation in the chromosome region 5p13.3-p13.2.

Name: brachydactyly type A1C
Definition: A brachydactyly type A1 has_material_basis_in homozygous or heterozygous mutation in the GDF5 gene on chromosome 20q11.

Name: brachydactyly type A1D
Definition: A brachydactyly type A1 that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the BMPR1B gene on chromosome 4q22.
